com.apercova.quickcsv

Class CsvReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apercova.quickcsv.CsvReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<List<String>>, Iterator<List<String>>

    public class CsvReader
extends Object
implements Closeable, Iterator<List<String>>, Iterable<List<String>>
    Reader for Comma-Separated values in compliance with RFC 4180 plus custom delimiter and quoted values. 
      Common Format and MIME Type for Comma-Separated Values (CSV) Files
  https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4180
    Version:
    1.0 2017.08
    Author:
    @apercova https://github.com/apercova

        public static List<List<String>> read(Reader reader)

        Core implementation for reading csv-values from a Reader. Default delimiter and quote chars are used in compliance with RFC 4180.
        Parameters:
        reader - Source for reading.
        Returns:
        List of read Csv lines.

      • read

        public static List<List<String>> read(Reader reader,
                                      char delimiter,
                                      char quote)
                               throws CsvReaderException
        Core implementation for reading csv-values from a Reader
        Parameters:
        reader - Source for reading.
        delimiter - Delimiter character. Default is a comma(,).
        quote - Quote character. Default is a double quote char(").
        Returns:
        List of read Csv lines.
        Throws:
        CsvReaderException - If an error happens whilst reading.
